Abdomen's not so soft now.

92
00:04:04,895 --> 00:04:07,145
Come on.

93
00:04:10,234 --> 00:04:13,068
It's full of blood.
It's full of blood.

94
00:04:13,103 --> 00:04:15,215
We got to find the
bleeding and stop it now.

95
00:04:15,239 --> 00:04:17,138
Hundley, call the OR.

96
00:04:17,941 --> 00:04:20,042
Hundley!

97
00:04:20,077 --> 00:04:22,911
- Page Neuro.
- How are the pupils?

98
00:04:22,946 --> 00:04:24,245
They're reactive, but...

99
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,227
We need Neuro.
Let's go. Come on.

100
00:04:28,251 --> 00:04:30,301
Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

101
00:04:30,336 --> 00:04:32,721
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

102
00:04:32,756 --> 00:04:34,222
How is she?

103
00:04:34,257 --> 00:04:36,424
Massive intra-abdominal
hemorrhage.

104
00:04:36,459 --> 00:04:38,893
- She's in good hands now.
- I got the page.

105
00:04:38,928 --> 00:04:40,762
What's with the audience?

106
00:04:40,797 --> 00:04:43,432
She's one of your scrub
nurses... Jessica Moore.

107
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:45,734
She's been in nearly
half of your surgeries.

108
00:04:45,769 --> 00:04:48,102
- She needs a head CT.
- No time. She'll bleed out

109
00:04:48,155 --> 00:04:49,632
on the CT table. We do this now.

110
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:51,618
I'll just put in an
extraventricular drain

111
00:04:51,642 --> 00:04:53,086
to measure pressure
and control the swelling.

112
00:04:53,110 --> 00:04:54,442
I can do that blind.

113
00:04:54,478 --> 00:04:55,844
Well, that's quite reassuring.

114
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:57,328
My job isn't to reassure you.

115
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:03,012
So, that's where we are.
Thanks for checking in.

116
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:04,831
- I'll keep you posted.
- Dr. Bell?

117
00:05:04,855 --> 00:05:07,005
- Yeah?
- How is she?

118
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:13,545
They're taking her for
an emergency ex-lap.

119
00:05:17,817 --> 00:05:19,446
This is on Red Rock.

120
00:05:19,470 --> 00:05:21,113
- I...
- They cut staff,

121
00:05:21,137 --> 00:05:23,366
overscheduled the OR, and
now Jessica's paying for it.

122
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:26,018
- We need more nurses.
- Can we just talk
about this later?

123
00:05:26,042 --> 00:05:28,143
No!

124
00:05:28,178 --> 00:05:30,623
We lost some of our
best due to the hours

125
00:05:30,647 --> 00:05:33,031
and salary cuts that
Red Rock instituted.

126
00:05:33,067 --> 00:05:35,211
- Uh...
- I have people working
a double shift right now.

127
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:37,147
- Do you want more Jessicas?
- No, of course not.

128
00:05:37,171 --> 00:05:38,964
I'm devastated by this. I...
You have... you have any idea

129
00:05:38,988 --> 00:05:41,456
how many hours I've
spent in an OR with Jessica?

130
00:05:41,491 --> 00:05:43,991
How many times she's had
my back in a tough surgery?

131
00:05:44,027 --> 00:05:47,028
Don't suggest that I don't
care what's happening to her.

132
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,315
She's not just a
member of my team.

133
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,334
She's like...
She's family to me.

134
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,574
Look...

135
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:01,988
I have one nurse today,
and she's a student.

136
00:06:02,012 --> 00:06:04,879
Even if she was fully trained,
that's not nearly enough.

137
00:06:04,932 --> 00:06:08,433
We can't keep doing
this. We need help.

138
00:06:09,753 --> 00:06:12,104
I'll see what I can do
about getting more nurses.

139
00:06:12,139 --> 00:06:14,121
Okay.

140
00:06:19,529 --> 00:06:21,012
Hey.

141
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:23,031
Hey, how is she?

142
00:06:26,135 --> 00:06:28,286
Cain and Raptor are
just getting started.

143
00:06:31,324 --> 00:06:33,375
Did you get ahold
of her parents?

144
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:36,944
They're on their way.

145
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:38,463
From Europe.

146
00:06:38,498 --> 00:06:42,133
They go twice a year...
Bordeaux and Tuscany.

147
00:06:42,169 --> 00:06:44,719
This is their, uh,
Bordeaux trip.

148
00:06:44,754 --> 00:06:47,372
Apparently, they're
really into wine.

149
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:50,308
She was going to introduce
me to them at Thanksgiving.

150
00:06:54,564 --> 00:06:58,099
Um... they're getting
on a plane right now.

151
00:06:58,152 --> 00:07:00,201
No contact for several hours.

152
00:07:00,236 --> 00:07:03,789
Have they designated a health
care proxy until they get here?

153
00:07:05,491 --> 00:07:07,442
Yes. Me.

154
00:07:07,494 --> 00:07:09,138
Good. Good choice.
You're a doctor.

155
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:10,640
Let me help you start
that paperwork, okay?

156
00:07:10,664 --> 00:07:13,298
No. No, no, no, no.

157
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,316
I'm not leaving her.

158
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:19,421
Irving, I know that
you are scared.

159
00:07:19,456 --> 00:07:21,173
Scared?

160
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:23,275
Scared does not cover it.

161
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,776
This is all my fault.

162
00:07:24,811 --> 00:07:27,728
How is this your fault?

163
00:07:27,764 --> 00:07:30,232
She's been pulling
doubles for days.

164
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:33,651
And then, we had
that game night.

165
00:07:33,686 --> 00:07:35,403
I knew she was exhausted.

166
00:07:35,438 --> 00:07:38,406
And... yesterday,

167
00:07:38,441 --> 00:07:40,475
she was heading out, and I...

168
00:07:49,169 --> 00:07:52,803
Okay. Five seconds of
action, and then I'm on the road.

169
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:55,268
Oh. Mmm.

170
00:07:57,144 --> 00:07:58,493
Usually, it's at least

171
00:07:58,528 --> 00:08:00,511
- ten seconds.
- Well...

172
00:08:00,547 --> 00:08:03,264
- You look tired.
- Thank you.

173
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,228
It's totally what a
girl wants to hear

174
00:08:05,252 --> 00:08:07,113
from a guy whose scrubs
she wants to get into.

175
00:08:07,137 --> 00:08:09,165
No, no, no. You know I
always think you're beautiful.

176
00:08:09,189 --> 00:08:11,050
- Mm-hmm.
- I'm just wondering
if you need a ride home.

177
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:13,791
Okay, least sexy
supply closet time ever.

178
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:15,187
I'm sorry.

179
00:08:15,211 --> 00:08:17,945
- Okay. Much better?
- Mm-hmm.

180
00:08:17,981 --> 00:08:20,315
I let her go.

181
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:22,367
No. No.

182
00:08:22,402 --> 00:08:24,535
You did not let her do anything.

183
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:26,804
This is not on you or her.

184
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:30,859
If you want to blame
someone, blame Red Rock.

185
00:08:30,894 --> 00:08:33,177
Assigning blame
doesn't help Jessica.

186
00:08:35,182 --> 00:08:37,143
Focus on what you can do now.

187
00:08:37,167 --> 00:08:39,384
Okay?

188
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,652
I will stay on the OR floor.

189
00:08:45,676 --> 00:08:48,376
I will be right here
to get updates.

190
00:08:48,411 --> 00:08:53,314
I will let you know as
soon as I hear anything.

191
00:08:53,350 --> 00:08:56,401
I will meet up with
you in the ICU.

192
00:09:00,274 --> 00:09:02,289
Go.

193
00:09:08,431 --> 00:09:10,615
Before we begin,
a quick gut check.

194
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:12,284
One of our own is on the table.

195
00:09:12,319 --> 00:09:14,268
Anyone too tired... physically

196
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:16,620
or emotionally...
Should step out now.

197
00:09:16,656 --> 00:09:18,556
Should I step out?

198
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:20,624
I worked two 30-hour
shifts this week.

199
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:24,095
Oh, wait. I'm the brain
surgeon. I should probably stay.

200
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:27,598
It's important that we are all
in tip-top shape for Jessica.

201
00:09:27,633 --> 00:09:30,117
So again, are we good?

202
00:09:31,805 --> 00:09:33,688
Nurse,

203
00:09:33,724 --> 00:09:35,551
how many shifts have
you had this week?

204
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,942
Not as many as Jessica.

205
00:09:37,978 --> 00:09:39,477
She, um...

206
00:09:41,281 --> 00:09:43,598
She covered for me yesterday.

207
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:47,602
Then I'm going to have
to ask you to step out.

208
00:09:47,637 --> 00:09:49,620
For Jessica.

209
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:53,073
Okay.

210
00:09:56,145 --> 00:09:58,780
That's a nice plan. Now
we're down a scrub nurse

211
00:09:58,832 --> 00:10:00,276
without enough
time to replace her.

212
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:02,784
- I'll do it.
- Aren't you a resident?

213
00:10:02,819 --> 00:10:05,386
I'm a surgeon. Surely I can
handle scrub nurse duties.

214
00:10:05,422 --> 00:10:07,555
Well, then it's settled.

215
00:10:07,590 --> 00:10:11,976
Nurse/Doctor Mina Okafor
is on the case. Let's go.

216
00:10:18,802 --> 00:10:21,419
How long have you
been in nursing school?

217
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:22,915
Uh, two years. I'm so excited

218
00:10:22,939 --> 00:10:24,800
to finally be here
in a real hospital.

219
00:10:24,824 --> 00:10:27,124
Can't wait to get into
the trenches, you know.

220
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,243
Really start
practicing medicine.

221
00:10:29,279 --> 00:10:32,513
Good, 'cause you're about
to hit the ground running.

222
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:35,349
We're working general
medicine and the ICU today.

223
00:10:35,384 --> 00:10:36,628
Wow. Is that, is that normal?

224
00:10:36,652 --> 00:10:38,469
No. It's a disaster.

225
00:10:38,505 --> 00:10:41,923
We're shorthanded, and we're
down one very important woman.

226
00:10:41,958 --> 00:10:43,308
I heard about the scrub nurse

227
00:10:43,343 --> 00:10:45,359
while I was filling
out my paperwork.

228
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:48,129
- I'm sorry. I hope she's okay.
- Me, too.

229
00:10:48,164 --> 00:10:49,792
I'll be going between
our patients and checking

230
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:52,433
on Jessica today, so... I
need you to keep up with me.

231
00:10:52,468 --> 00:10:54,002
Oh, yeah. I'll try.

232
00:10:54,037 --> 00:10:56,704
- Oh, my God.
- Dad.

233
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:58,772
Ah. Oh, I heard
there was an accident,

234
00:10:58,808 --> 00:11:01,159
a Chastain nurse.
I was terrified.

235
00:11:01,194 --> 00:11:02,626
Well, I'm fine.

236
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:04,290
Okay, you can let go now.

237
00:11:04,314 --> 00:11:05,646
All right.

238
00:11:05,682 --> 00:11:07,460
I'm okay. Uh, this is,

239
00:11:07,484 --> 00:11:09,212
uh, Clara. She's
our student nurse.

240
00:11:09,236 --> 00:11:10,329
- Hi.
- That's my dad, Kyle Nevin.

241
00:11:10,353 --> 00:11:11,680
I will update you
on Jessica later,

242
00:11:11,704 --> 00:11:13,020
but right now I got to go.

243
00:11:13,055 --> 00:11:15,306
Hey, hey, hey. I can help.

244
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:16,958
Uh...

245
00:11:16,993 --> 00:11:18,821
Isn't it pretty great?

