honored, Dr. Bell.

503
00:22:46,132 --> 00:22:48,012
I know how much
she respects you.

504
00:22:52,371 --> 00:22:54,287
All right.

505
00:23:09,421 --> 00:23:10,821
Hey.

506
00:23:22,969 --> 00:23:25,452
What can I get you, Dr. Feldman?

507
00:23:28,140 --> 00:23:30,107
Uh, his usual.

508
00:23:30,142 --> 00:23:31,492
Tri-tip sandwich coming up.

509
00:23:32,562 --> 00:23:34,644
You don't look so good.

510
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:35,645
Go sit.

511
00:23:35,681 --> 00:23:38,065
Grab that free table, okay?

512
00:23:40,336 --> 00:23:43,270
We may need to get a social
worker to come talk to him.

513
00:23:44,489 --> 00:23:46,790
Get him something
for his anxiety.

514
00:23:46,825 --> 00:23:49,559
He needs to keep a clear head.

515
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:50,811
Let's get some food in him.

516
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:52,396
We're out of tri-tip.

517
00:23:52,431 --> 00:23:54,131
Tuna salad?

518
00:23:54,166 --> 00:23:56,983
It's tri-tip day.

519
00:23:57,019 --> 00:24:00,771
The man needs
a tri-tip sandwich.

520
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:02,423
He doesn't like tuna salad.

521
00:24:02,458 --> 00:24:03,791
Do you understand?

522
00:24:03,843 --> 00:24:06,693
So go back there
and get some tri-tip!

523
00:24:11,184 --> 00:24:13,267
We're all having a bad day.

524
00:24:16,005 --> 00:24:17,654
That was uncalled for.

525
00:24:17,689 --> 00:24:18,822
I'm sorry.

526
00:24:18,857 --> 00:24:20,302
It's okay.

527
00:24:20,326 --> 00:24:22,743
I heard about Jessica.

528
00:24:22,778 --> 00:24:23,943
I understand.

529
00:24:23,996 --> 00:24:26,830
We're all in it together.

530
00:24:35,657 --> 00:24:37,274
What's going on?

531
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:39,460
Got more labs back.

532
00:24:39,495 --> 00:24:41,311
Platelets are still falling,

533
00:24:41,347 --> 00:24:42,774
and now she's anemic,
so I paged Austin.

534
00:24:42,798 --> 00:24:45,015
That doesn't make any sense.

535
00:24:45,050 --> 00:24:47,613
She's gotten over
20 units PRBCs,

536
00:24:47,637 --> 00:24:49,498
15 FFPs, ten
units of platelets...

537
00:24:49,522 --> 00:24:51,400
Yeah, well, you better
keep 'em coming.

538
00:24:51,424 --> 00:24:52,451
You think she's still bleeding?

539
00:24:52,475 --> 00:24:53,719
I don't see anything
in her chest.

540
00:24:53,743 --> 00:24:54,802
Her belly's nice and soft.

541
00:24:54,826 --> 00:24:56,706
Well, where's all
the blood going?

542
00:24:58,147 --> 00:24:59,947
We're working on that.

543
00:24:59,982 --> 00:25:02,115
You're sure you didn't
miss a bleed somewhere?

544
00:25:02,151 --> 00:25:04,045
Maybe the retroperitoneum
or pleural cavities?

545
00:25:04,069 --> 00:25:05,452
No, I didn't miss anything.

546
00:25:05,487 --> 00:25:08,071
You can't know
that. Maybe, this time,

547
00:25:08,107 --> 00:25:09,684
you missed something and
that's why Jessica's still too sick

548
00:25:09,708 --> 00:25:11,637
for surgery. And now
she's running out of time.

549
00:25:11,661 --> 00:25:14,210
Hey. Remember, we
are on the same side.

550
00:25:14,246 --> 00:25:17,064
I'll take her for another CT,

551
00:25:17,099 --> 00:25:19,094
just to make sure we're
not missing anything.

552
00:25:19,118 --> 00:25:22,052
I didn't miss anything.

553
00:25:22,088 --> 00:25:24,838
But let's get another
CT, so we can be certain.

554
00:25:24,891 --> 00:25:26,707
I'm sorry I left you, babe.

555
00:25:26,759 --> 00:25:28,792
I'm sorry.

556
00:25:40,723 --> 00:25:43,357
What's going on?

557
00:25:44,460 --> 00:25:46,076
She's still anemic

558
00:25:46,112 --> 00:25:48,256
and thrombocytopenic
despite multiple transfusions.

559
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,846
Why?

560
00:25:49,882 --> 00:25:51,264
I'm working on it.

561
00:25:53,652 --> 00:25:55,769
Honestly, I don't know.

562
00:25:55,805 --> 00:25:57,237
There's nothing on the CT?

563
00:25:57,272 --> 00:25:58,672
No.

564
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:06,463
I called the CEO of DiaCure.

565
00:26:06,499 --> 00:26:07,781
We made a deal.

566
00:26:07,817 --> 00:26:11,301
We're gonna use their
dialysis equipment exclusively.

567
00:26:13,789 --> 00:26:16,640
You can get the data you need.

568
00:26:17,626 --> 00:26:19,276
I-I just, uh...

569
00:26:19,311 --> 00:26:22,245
just felt like I had to
do something positive.

570
00:26:24,566 --> 00:26:28,101
J-Jessica's...

571
00:26:28,136 --> 00:26:33,072
She's my favorite
of the OR nurses.

572
00:26:33,125 --> 00:26:34,302
You know, she's
a... She's a pistol.

573
00:26:34,326 --> 00:26:37,744
You know. And...

574
00:26:37,797 --> 00:26:40,630
sweet.

575
00:26:40,665 --> 00:26:42,916
And a lady.

576
00:26:46,588 --> 00:26:49,423
So this one's for her.

577
00:26:52,762 --> 00:26:56,079
Wish it were more.

578
00:26:56,114 --> 00:26:58,515
It's all I got.

579
00:27:00,368 --> 00:27:02,486
Thank you.

580
00:27:07,676 --> 00:27:09,826
Your dressing
needs to be changed.

581
00:27:09,862 --> 00:27:11,628
Get me a real nurse.

582
00:27:11,663 --> 00:27:13,174
He's been picking
at his cellulitis.

583
00:27:13,198 --> 00:27:15,177
Yeah, bec... I can't
help it, because it itches.

584
00:27:15,201 --> 00:27:16,812
All right? So why don't... Why
don't you give me something

585
00:27:16,836 --> 00:27:18,146
in-instead of
getting in my face?

586
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:20,370
That sounds like drug
seeking to me, and...

587
00:27:20,405 --> 00:27:22,351
- Sir, you can't-can't do that.
- Steve.

588
00:27:22,375 --> 00:27:25,303
Sir. Sir...
- You need to get back in bed. Hey, hey.

589
00:27:25,327 --> 00:27:27,356
Steve, come on. You
got to get back in bed.

590
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:29,863
Nic!

591
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:31,893
The meth head is
trying to kill your father!

592
00:27:31,917 --> 00:27:33,695
The meth head is
trying to kill your father!

593
00:27:33,719 --> 00:27:35,819
Help! Hey, hey, hey!

594
00:27:38,974 --> 00:27:40,624
Code gray!

595
00:27:44,546 --> 00:27:46,613
- Hey, hey.
- Hey, hey, hey.

596
00:27:46,649 --> 00:27:48,682
- Ow! Oh!
- Hey! Hey!

597
00:27:48,717 --> 00:27:50,483
Ow! Ow! Ow, ow! Ow, ow, ow!

598
00:27:50,518 --> 00:27:52,169
Hold him down!

599
00:27:52,204 --> 00:27:53,632
Let go of me!

600
00:27:57,325 --> 00:27:59,220
- Dad, are you okay?
- Yeah. He bit me.

601
00:27:59,244 --> 00:28:00,627
Is that bad?

602
00:28:00,663 --> 00:28:02,307
He didn't break the skin,
but we'll take a look at it,

603
00:28:02,331 --> 00:28:05,549
just in case.

604
00:28:05,584 --> 00:28:07,896
- It's okay.
- Oh, it's a good... it was a good thing I was here.

605
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:09,420
Right place at the right time.

606
00:28:09,455 --> 00:28:12,506
He could've hurt... uh, Clara.

607
00:28:12,541 --> 00:28:14,007
Clara, I'm sorry.

608
00:28:14,042 --> 00:28:15,186
I shouldn't have left you alone.

609
00:28:15,210 --> 00:28:16,192
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

610
00:28:16,228 --> 00:28:17,193
Yeah, I'm fine.

611
00:28:17,229 --> 00:28:18,606
Ooh, ooh.

612
00:28:18,630 --> 00:28:20,380
He s-spit on me.

613
00:28:20,415 --> 00:28:23,032
Oh, God.

614
00:28:33,579 --> 00:28:34,778
You okay?

615
00:28:34,813 --> 00:28:36,947
Yeah, it's fine. I'm fine.

616
00:28:36,982 --> 00:28:39,599
It's okay not to be fine.

617
00:28:39,635 --> 00:28:41,846
Nursing school doesn't
prepare you for a day like this.

618
00:28:41,870 --> 00:28:42,935
I quit.

619
00:28:52,397 --> 00:28:53,547
You can't.

620
00:28:53,582 --> 00:28:55,098
I'm sorry.

621
00:28:55,133 --> 00:28:58,602
I'm short of nurses, and I
need everybody that I can get.

622
00:29:00,806 --> 00:29:03,240
Plus...

623
00:29:03,275 --> 00:29:04,791
you can do this.

624
00:29:04,826 --> 00:29:06,809
I don't want to.

625
00:29:06,845 --> 00:29:09,596
I mean...

626
00:29:09,631 --> 00:29:12,766
it was one thing
when it was on paper.

627
00:29:12,801 --> 00:29:15,786
What are the warning
signs of heart failure?

628
00:29:15,821 --> 00:29:17,988
How many milliliters?

629
00:29:18,023 --> 00:29:20,607
I liked studying medicine.

630
00:29:20,642 --> 00:29:22,126
But when it comes to this...

631
00:29:22,161 --> 00:29:26,329
Look, you've had a
seriously difficult first day.

632
00:29:26,365 --> 00:29:28,981
But, hey, at least no
one threw up on you.

633
00:29:29,017 --> 00:29:31,146
No one pulled a chunk
of hair out of your head.

634
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:32,635
That happened to you?

635
00:29:32,671 --> 00:29:34,120
First day.

636
00:29:34,156 --> 00:29:37,090
God, why do you do this?

637
00:29:38,343 --> 00:29:41,294
Look, we don't have
to like all of our patients.

638
00:29:41,330 --> 00:29:43,513
But we do have to
take care of them.

639
00:29:43,549 --> 00:29:45,748
Because, whoever they are,

640
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:48,435
they're sick and in pain.

641
00:29:48,470 --> 00:29:50,954
And it's our job
to deal with it.

642
00:29:50,989 --> 00:29:54,307
And sometimes,
yes, it is so hard.

643
00:29:54,342 --> 00:29:56,326
But...

644
00:29:56,362 --> 00:30:00,914
not many people get a
chance to make a difference.

645
00:30:00,950 --> 00:30:03,250
A good nurse can.

646
00:30:05,854 --> 00:30:08,305
You've invested...

647
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:10,457
two years in this?

648
00:30:10,492 --> 00:30:13,092
Student debt, I imagine?

649
00:30:13,128 --> 00:30:16,296
You can always quit
on your second day.

650
00:30:17,349 --> 00:30:19,766
Come on.

651
00:30:19,802 --> 00:30:21,168
You got this. Let's go.

652
00:30:25,857 --> 00:30:27,168
You figure out what's going
on with her blood counts?

653
00:30:27,192 --> 00:30:28,458
No.

654
00:30:28,494 --> 00:30:29,442
Her ICP keeps going up.

655
00:30:29,477 --> 00:30:31,060
We don't have any more time.

656
00:30:31,096 --> 00:30:33,057
You delayed this surgery
for no good reason.

657
00:30:33,081 --> 00:30:34,047
You failed.

658
00:30:34,082 --> 00:30:35,566
Self-important neophyte,

659
00:30:35,601 --> 00:30:37,561
you don't even know
how much you don't know.

660
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:39,414
I'm gonna remove the
pressure from her brain

661
00:30:39,438 --> 00:30:41,416
and hope it's not too
late. So, congratulations.

662
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:44,424
Your narcissism almost
killed your patient.

663
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:55,702
Saw to me.

664
00:31:05,414 --> 00:31:07,008
Are you sure you're
okay to be here?

665
00:31:07,032 --> 00:31:08,577
This is the last place
on earth I want to be,

666
00:31:08,601 --> 00:31:09,883
and I won't be anywhere else.

667
00:31:25,467 --> 00:31:26,800
Scalpel.

668
00:31:32,774 --> 00:31:35,375
Lap pads. Cautery.

669
00:31:35,410 --> 00:31:37,610
- There's too much blood.
- Get suction in, damn it.

670
00:31:38,062 --> 00:31:39,796
Suction.

671
00:31:41,483 --> 00:31:42,849
Oh, my God. No.

672
00:31:42,884 --> 00:31:45,852
This is exactly what
Conrad said would happen.

673
00:31:45,887 --> 00:31:47,353
Why isn't she clotting?

674
00:31:47,388 --> 00:31:48,955
Hey, man,

675
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:50,907
we didn't have a choice anymore.

676
00:31:50,943 --> 00:31:52,737
When you wait too
long, her brain swells

677
00:31:52,761 --> 00:31:54,895
and she dies. You
go back in there

678
00:31:54,930 --> 00:31:58,147
without correcting her
coagulopathy, she bleeds out.

679
00:31:58,183 --> 00:31:59,716
It was my job to figure it out.

680
00:31:59,751 --> 00:32:01,484
Maybe we still can.

681
00:32:02,971 --> 00:32:04,871
Let's work on the differential.

682
00:32:04,906 --> 00:32:06,489
Together.

683
00:32:07,493 --> 00:32:08,720
Okay.

684
00:32:08,744 --> 00:32:11,210
All right, she's
bleeding. It won't stop.

685
00:32:11,246 --> 00:32:12,879
Why?

686
00:32:12,914 --> 00:32:14,309
- And where does the blood go?
- Into the body

687
00:32:14,333 --> 00:32:15,643
- or onto the floor.
- In this case, neither.

688
00:32:15,667 --> 00:32:18,284
Jessica's not losing platelets.

689
00:32:18,319 --> 00:32:19,463
Her body is destroying them.

690
00:32:19,487 --> 00:32:22,722
Hemolysis, low platelets,

691
00:32:22,758 --> 00:32:24,224
renal dysfunction, fever.

692
00:32:24,259 --> 00:32:26,460
- It's got to be TTP.
- Oh, God.

693
00:32:26,512 --> 00:32:28,907
If she has TTP, her platelet
count will just keep dropping.

694
00:32:28,931 --> 00:32:30,397
She'll never clot.

695
00:32:30,432 --> 00:32:31,859
This surgery is
going to kill her,

696
00:32:31,883 --> 00:32:33,510
and I gave the okay
to go ahead with it.

697
00:32:33,534 --> 00:32:35,501
Now that we know what it is,

698
00:32:35,537 --> 00:32:36,853
we can treat it.

699
00:32:36,888 --> 00:32:38,855
So you're gonna
start plasmapheresis

700
00:32:38,891 --> 00:32:40,290
while she's in surgery?

701
00:32:43,162 --> 00:32:45,395
Hell yeah, he is.

702
00:32:48,834 --> 00:32:50,478
<i>Move faster. Get that bleeder.</i>

703
00:32:50,502 --> 00:32:52,869
I'm moving as fast as I
can. It's oozing everywhere.

704
00:32:52,905 --> 00:32:54,105
Keep hanging those platelets.

705
00:32:55,674 --> 00:32:57,123
Get out of my OR! Now!

706
00:32:59,827 --> 00:33:01,127
<i>I'm chief of surgery.</i>

707
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:03,313
<i>Every OR in Chastain is my OR.</i>

708
00:33:03,349 --> 00:33:04,798
<i>Hawkins stays.</i>

709
00:33:04,833 --> 00:33:06,695
- What's happening?
- Jessica has TTP.

710
00:33:06,719 --> 00:33:09,531
- Giving her more platelets
won't help.
- Scrub nurse, ignore him.

711
00:33:09,555 --> 00:33:12,656
- I need you with me
on this cautery.
- All you.

712
00:33:12,691 --> 00:33:14,518
- Conrad, I'll get access.
- Thank you.

713
00:33:14,542 --> 00:33:16,709
You can do that
plasmapheresis when I'm done.

714
00:33:19,815 --> 00:33:21,126
You have no idea
even if you're right,

715
00:33:21,150 --> 00:33:23,166
let alone if it's gonna help.

716
00:33:33,545 --> 00:33:35,679
Okay, now we can cauterize.

717
00:33:39,668 --> 00:33:41,184
Now she has a chance.

718
00:33:49,728 --> 00:33:53,179
Dr. Bell, just wanted
to congratulate you.

719
00:33:53,214 --> 00:33:54,681
What for?

720
00:33:54,716 --> 00:33:57,266
Heard you made a
very lucrative deal today.

721
00:33:57,302 --> 00:33:58,779
- DiaCure Dialysis Centers.
- Yeah.

722
00:33:58,803 --> 00:34:01,104
They gave us a great
price for exclusivity.

723
00:34:01,139 --> 00:34:03,874
That deserves an
"attaboy" from the new veep.

724
00:34:03,909 --> 00:34:06,221
What kind of kickback did
they offer us for the contract?

725
00:34:06,245 --> 00:34:09,662
Some data we required
for patient safety,

726
00:34:09,697 --> 00:34:12,010
and they committed to help
us with the money we need

727
00:34:12,034 --> 00:34:13,677
- to fill out our nursing staff.
- Whoa.

728
00:34:13,701 --> 00:34:15,613
Punching above
your weight there.

729
00:34:15,637 --> 00:34:17,265
I'll make the call on
where the money goes.

730
00:34:17,289 --> 00:34:18,721
I'm thinking Neuro.

731
00:34:18,757 --> 00:34:21,007
Barrett's got a laundry
list of line items.

732
00:34:21,042 --> 00:34:22,525
Barrett?

733
00:34:22,561 --> 00:34:24,288
You on a first-name
basis with Dr. Cain?

734
00:34:24,312 --> 00:34:26,946
We go way back. He's
the one who got me this job.

735
00:34:26,981 --> 00:34:29,799
Lured me away from a
hedge fund on the West Coast.

736
00:34:31,970 --> 00:34:34,532
You have no
background in health care.

737
00:34:34,556 --> 00:34:38,074
I have a
background... in profits.

738
00:34:39,928 --> 00:34:41,956
Well, this profit
goes for more nurses.

739
00:34:41,980 --> 00:34:43,774
It's... it's part of
the agreement.

740
00:34:43,798 --> 00:34:45,164
It can't be undone.

741
00:34:46,785 --> 00:34:49,635
No more deals like this
again without my input.

742
00:35:01,333 --> 00:35:04,094
Hey. I'm just gonna
change the dressing.

743
00:35:07,122 --> 00:35:09,839
All right, let's see
what we have.

744
00:35:19,651 --> 00:35:23,286
There isn't very much
blood around the incision.

745
00:35:23,322 --> 00:35:24,804
It's starting to clot.

746
00:35:26,357 --> 00:35:28,124
We'll get another CBC.

747
00:35:30,829 --> 00:35:33,980
Yeah, well, we can send
it in, but this is good news.

748
00:35:34,015 --> 00:35:35,966
The plasmapheresis is working.

749
00:35:36,001 --> 00:35:38,685
She still might not wake up.

750
00:35:40,022 --> 00:35:42,288
And if she does,

751
00:35:42,323 --> 00:35:44,468
we have no idea what
kind of shape she'll be in.

752
00:35:44,492 --> 00:35:47,510
We'll know more in 24 hours.

753
00:35:58,023 --> 00:36:00,490
- Hey, Dad, wait.
- Oh, Nic.

754
00:36:00,525 --> 00:36:02,225
I just finished my shift.

755
00:36:02,261 --> 00:36:05,328
- You need something?
- Look, um...

756
00:36:05,363 --> 00:36:07,323
Thanks for being here today.

757
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:10,516
I love volunteering.

758
00:36:14,039 --> 00:36:17,390
I know you were scared
that it was me when you heard

759
00:36:17,426 --> 00:36:19,375
about the accident this morning.

760
00:36:19,410 --> 00:36:20,827
I brushed you off.

761
00:36:20,879 --> 00:36:23,880
I'm sorry I did that.

762
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:30,753
You're all I got, kid.

763
00:36:40,114 --> 00:36:42,031
We're Team Nevin now.

764
00:37:04,272 --> 00:37:06,923
Still no change in Jessica.

765
00:37:10,978 --> 00:37:12,428
What's this?

766
00:37:14,149 --> 00:37:16,299
DiaCure records.

767
00:37:16,335 --> 00:37:18,969
You got them.

768
00:37:19,004 --> 00:37:20,436
Yeah.

769
00:37:21,973 --> 00:37:23,573
It's worse than we thought.

770
00:37:23,608 --> 00:37:26,776
20% higher complication
rate with Hemopleatin.

771
00:37:28,229 --> 00:37:30,029
Look at all these PEs.

772
00:37:31,900 --> 00:37:34,267
This drug is probably
what killed Jessie.

773
00:37:34,302 --> 00:37:35,952
I think so.

774
00:37:37,639 --> 00:37:40,807
What do you think
the next step is?

775
00:37:42,411 --> 00:37:44,238
Tomorrow I go in to
see Bell and Red Rock,

776
00:37:44,262 --> 00:37:46,302
and get this drug
pulled off the shelves.

777
00:37:46,331 --> 00:37:48,397
Permanently.

778
00:37:48,433 --> 00:37:51,134
You know how
dangerous that is, Conrad?

779
00:37:51,169 --> 00:37:53,119
Big Pharma is ruthless.

780
00:37:53,154 --> 00:37:54,804
They could go after you.

781
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:57,440
They always like to
discredit the messenger.

782
00:37:57,475 --> 00:37:58,758
The numbers don't lie.

783
00:37:58,810 --> 00:38:00,154
We'll make sure what
happened to Jessie

784
00:38:00,178 --> 00:38:02,161
doesn't happen to anyone else.

785
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:07,017
Her death could save lives.

786
00:38:18,496 --> 00:38:21,681
As awful as this is, I
learned something today.

787
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:27,820
I really love her.

788
00:38:27,873 --> 00:38:29,517
I don't think I
realized how much

789
00:38:29,541 --> 00:38:31,421
until I thought I
might lose her.

790
00:38:35,897 --> 00:38:40,183
If she comes back
to me, I'll tell her.

791
00:38:43,522 --> 00:38:46,239
Please come back to me.

792
00:38:48,026 --> 00:38:50,960
We all see how much
you guys love each other.

793
00:38:50,996 --> 00:38:52,695
You know, I beat myself up

794
00:38:52,730 --> 00:38:54,964
about leaving
Priya at the altar.

795
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:58,518
But now I know it was right.

796
00:38:58,553 --> 00:39:03,123
Because what we
had... it wasn't this.

797
00:39:03,158 --> 00:39:06,075
Don't make this
about you, Pravesh.

798
00:39:07,596 --> 00:39:08,744
Hey.

799
00:39:11,732 --> 00:39:13,416
Thank you.

800
00:39:14,686 --> 00:39:16,002
Oh!

801
00:39:16,037 --> 00:39:17,854
- Um, okay.
- It's happening.

802
00:39:17,889 --> 00:39:19,339
Give into it.

803
00:39:19,374 --> 00:39:21,391
- Oh, that's tight. But...
- Yeah.

804
00:39:21,426 --> 00:39:23,592
Come on. There you go.

805
00:39:23,628 --> 00:39:25,011
Oh, buddy.

806
00:39:29,067 --> 00:39:32,218
Hmm, you're certain you
have enough patient information

807
00:39:32,270 --> 00:39:36,672
to prove that Hemopleatin
is causing sudden death

808
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:38,552
in a significant
number of patients?

809
00:39:38,576 --> 00:39:40,109
Yes.

810
00:39:40,144 --> 00:39:43,162
We need to pull it
immediately and warn the FDA.

811
00:39:43,198 --> 00:39:45,359
No, I've looked over the
data; Dr. Hawkins is right.

812
00:39:45,383 --> 00:39:48,179
The complication
rate is off the charts.

813
00:39:48,203 --> 00:39:50,920
I'll-I'll have my people
go over the figures,

814
00:39:50,956 --> 00:39:52,555
and if this checks out,

815
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:55,391
we'll use it to
make a PR splash.

816
00:39:55,426 --> 00:39:59,228
Chastain catches a deadly drug

817
00:39:59,264 --> 00:40:01,375
- and saves patients.
- And in the meantime,

818
00:40:01,399 --> 00:40:04,417
we can go back to using an
older drug that we know to be safe.

819
00:40:04,469 --> 00:40:06,080
And, more good news,
it's actually cheaper.

820
00:40:06,104 --> 00:40:09,538
Well, that's a huge
win on all fronts.

821
00:40:09,574 --> 00:40:12,241
- Really nice work.
- All right.

822
00:40:12,277 --> 00:40:13,676
Thank you.

823
00:40:14,779 --> 00:40:16,312
That info...

824
00:40:16,348 --> 00:40:19,883
was part of the DiaCure deal.

825
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:21,734
So you helped him?

826
00:40:21,770 --> 00:40:23,269
Yeah. Yeah.

827
00:40:23,304 --> 00:40:26,956
But I'm happy to let the
hospital take the credit.

828
00:40:28,860 --> 00:40:31,811
Okay.

829
00:40:54,485 --> 00:40:55,885
Wake up.

830
00:40:59,491 --> 00:41:00,756
Me or her?

831
00:41:00,792 --> 00:41:01,991
Both, I think.

832
00:41:02,026 --> 00:41:04,243
- Mm.
- Jess? Honey?

833
00:41:04,279 --> 00:41:05,828
- Jess?
- Mm.

834
00:41:05,863 --> 00:41:08,114
Can you hear me?

835
00:41:08,166 --> 00:41:10,461
- Mm.
- Can you hear me? Hey. Hey.

836
00:41:10,485 --> 00:41:12,630
- Hey. Hey, hey. Whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Careful, careful.

837
00:41:12,654 --> 00:41:13,797
Shh, shh. No, don't do that.

838
00:41:13,821 --> 00:41:15,332
- You're okay. Hey.
- Hey, Jess.

839
00:41:15,356 --> 00:41:16,789
Honey.

840
00:41:16,842 --> 00:41:18,007
Hey. You're okay.

841
00:41:18,042 --> 00:41:19,825
You're fine. You're fine.

842
00:41:21,630 --> 00:41:25,815
It's a long story, but
everything's gonna be just fine.

843
00:41:31,189 --> 00:41:34,490
Okay. Here we go. Here we go.

844
00:41:34,525 --> 00:41:36,120
You could use
some vittles in ya.

845
00:41:36,144 --> 00:41:37,488
All right. I'll eat now.

846
00:41:37,512 --> 00:41:39,978
- This is a mess.
- Do the honors.

847
00:41:40,031 --> 00:41:41,792
- This looks good.
- Yeah, this is not
from the cafeteria.

848
00:41:41,816 --> 00:41:43,460
Okay, I want the little
baby one over here.

849
00:41:43,484 --> 00:41:45,568
I heard the good news.

850
00:41:45,603 --> 00:41:48,670
- Dr. Hawkins, a word?
- Yeah, sure thing.

851
00:41:54,329 --> 00:41:57,646
I just want to say, I, uh,
appreciate what you did,

852
00:41:57,682 --> 00:41:59,676
and I actually regret
that we had words.

853
00:41:59,700 --> 00:42:01,696
It-it was an emotional
day for all of us.

854
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:04,253
No doubt. No doubt.

855
00:42:04,288 --> 00:42:06,939
But don't ever question
my decision again.

856
00:42:09,527 --> 00:42:11,644
Well, when I'm wrong,

857
00:42:11,679 --> 00:42:13,374
I've learned to listen
to my colleagues.

858
00:42:13,398 --> 00:42:14,764
You're not a colleague.

859
00:42:14,799 --> 00:42:16,394
You're a subordinate
and I don't give a damn

860
00:42:16,418 --> 00:42:17,717
what your process is.

861
00:42:17,752 --> 00:42:19,869
You're not invincible, you know.

862
00:42:21,589 --> 00:42:23,973
No one is.

863
00:42:25,443 --> 00:42:27,126
You sure about that?

864
00:42:42,994 --> 00:42:44,744
We on the same page?

865
00:42:45,796 --> 00:42:48,047
You tell me.

866
00:42:48,082 --> 00:42:50,916
Hawkins is a whistleblower.

867
00:42:50,951 --> 00:42:55,388
My concern is him deciding
in his self-righteous way

868
00:42:55,423 --> 00:42:58,891
that Red Rock is doing
something he doesn't like.

869
00:42:58,926 --> 00:43:01,644
That's not something
I can live with.

870
00:43:02,964 --> 00:43:04,647
Then there's our answer.

871
00:43:06,568 --> 00:43:08,934
He's a threat to the hospital.

872
00:43:09,970 --> 00:43:13,239
I'll handle it.

873
